This case was not selected for publication in the Federal Reporter

Note: Pursuant to Fed. Cir. R. 47.6, this order is not citable as precedent.

It is a public order.

Clark W. MOORE, Petitioner, v. DEPARTMENT OF THE INTERIOR, Respondent. No. 2006-3364. United States Court of Appeals, Federal Circuit. Oct. 12, 2006. Clark W. Moore, pro se.

ORDER

The petitioner having failed to pay the docketing fee required by Federal Circuit Rule 52(a)(1) within the time permitted by the rules, it is

ORDERED that the petition for review be, and the same hereby is, DISMISSED, for failure to prosecute in accordance with the rules.
